                        </h4>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingFour">
                        <div class="panel-body">
                            California public libraries engaged in cooperative efforts with neighboring libraries are supported through state funding provided through the <a href="/services/to-libraries/ca-library-services-act/about/">California Library Services Act (CLSA)</a>, specifically designed to assist and encourage such interlibrary cooperation. The program is administered by the 13-member California Library Services Board. Funding is allocated to California Cooperative Library Systems.
                        </div>
                    </div>
